N.B.
LBNP can send /search with category "Standard Delivery" or "Express Delivery" and the LSP is required to respond with all appropriate options e.g. for "Standard Delivery", the LSP responds with options for "Immediate Delivery", "Same Day Delivery", "Next Day Delivery", as applicable;
LBNP can also send /search for specific category such as "Immediate Delivery", "Same Day Delivery", "Next Day Delivery" and the LSP either responds with options available or doesn’t respond;
Catalog response provided by LSP can be either "P2P" (point-to-point) or "P2H2P" (point-to-hub-to-point), corresponding to Context.domain:
for "P2P", the rider delivers the package directly from the pickup location (merchant’s) to the drop-off location (buyer’s), for "P2H2P", the package is routed through a hub;
LBNP can inform the merchants of the type of packaging required, based on the fulfillment option i.e. "P2P" or "P2H2P". Since "P2H2P" fulfillments are routed through a hub, AWB no is required;
For different logistics categories, following validations should be in place:
"Immediate Delivery" - time.duration <= PT60M for the same day (time.timestamp is same day as Context.timestamp);
"Same Day Delivery" - for the same day(time.timestamp is same day as Context.timestamp)[n][o];
"Next Day Delivery" - for the next day (time.timestamp is the day after the day for Context.timestamp);
