N.B.
/on_confirm returns the fulfillment slot, agent details, vehicle details, E-way bill no, as applicable, for inter-state shipments;
Rules for order confirmation
/confirm and /on_confirm calls should be idempotent;
LBNP will create the order id which will be unique across the network. In response to /confirm from LBNP, LSP sends /on_confirm with the same order_id;
LBNP sends /confirm, LSP validates[181]order:
if validation successful, LSP responds with ACK and creates order;
if validation not successful, LSP responds with NACK with error code 66002 (order validation failure):
after LBNP receives NACK, they should cancel the order withreason code996 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure);
if this order is passed in subsequent API calls (/confirm, /status, /cancel, /update, etc.), LSP returns NACK with error code 66004 (order not found);
LSP may also respond with NACK due to other internal errors (http 504, retriable error code 66001):
LBNP should retry[182]/confirm. If after the retry interval, LBNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 996;
if LBNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should retry /confirm (same as above). If within the retry interval, LBNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 996;
LSP sends /on_confirm, LBNP validates[183]order:
if validation successful, LBNP responds with ACK;
if validation not successful, LBNP responds with NACK with error code 63002 (order validation failure):
after LSP receives NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 997 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure)& push the status change to LBNP;
if this order (with cancellation state & reason code) is passed in subsequent API calls (/on_confirm, /on_status, /on_cancel, /on_update), LBNP responds with ACK;
LBNP may also NACK due to internal errors (http 504/503, retriable error code 63001):
LSP should retry[184]/on_confirm. If after the retry interval, LSP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code 997;
If order is passed in subsequent API calls within the retry window (/status, /track, /cancel, /update), LSP responds with current order state along with error code 66003 (order processing in progress);
If order is passed in subsequent API calls after cancellation (/status, /cancel, /update), LSP sends response with order state as cancelled;
