Feature discovery - 000
Dynamic mechanism for LBNP & LSP to mutually discover the features supported:
All features supported by the protocol will be documented as part of the API contract;
Features will be of 2 types:
"Baseline" - to be supported by all NPs;
"Enhanced" - NPs may prioritize & enable specific features, as per their business requirements;
LSP will communicate the list of "enhanced" features that are supported, as part of /on_search:
LBNP will need to maintain the list of features supported by each LSP, so that order & post-order flows for a specific LBNP can complete successfully;
In case LBNP sends payload for a function not supported by a LSP, LSP can NACK the response with error code 61001;
Some of the "enhanced" features result in LSP sending unsolicited information to LBNP (e.g. "Updated cancellation codes" (00B):
for these features, LBNP to also communicate the list of "enhanced" features supported;
these features are identified, in the list of features, with "Published by LBNP" = "Yes";
In case LSP sends payload for a function not supported by a LBNP, LBNP can NACK the response with error code 64001;
New features will mostly start as "enhanced", but may move to "baseline" in a future version;
With every change in the "baseline" list, context.core_version will be updated;
Feature list ishere;
