RTO (with return) - 022
LSP that handles RTO, with return, publishes this as an operational capability:
LBNP identifies fulfillment for return using "return_to_origin";
RTO, with return, will result in package being returned to the point of pickup (for now);
If the RTO request is valid (as determined by the reason code and other info provided), LBNP has to accept the request. If LSP sends a different quote, from what was sent in /on_search, LBNP may reject the RTO request (with NACK and error code 62503) and the RTO request has to be resent with the correct quote;
In case of on-network logistics, /on_cancel will also result in cascaded retail /on_cancel request, for the fulfillment, and include the new fulfillment record for RTO, fulfillment start location / time, fulfillment state, order state and quote for RTO (if retail buyer has to pay for the RTO cost as per the cancellation reason code);
